This kernel assigns each thread to one spatial position (batch, dim1, dim2). Each thread then:
1. Iterates through all features to compute sum of squares
2. Computes RMS = sqrt(mean + eps)
3. Normalizes all feature values at that position

This approach provides good parallelism since we have batch_size × dim1 × dim2 = 112 × 512 × 512 = ~29M independent work units.

